                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370130-name-722" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370130-name-722" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370130-name-722" type="surname" value="MURRAT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370130-name-722" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN MURRAT</persName>
                  </hi>. I had a pair of unmade trowsers given to me by Mrs. Handley on the 5th of January, between eight and nine o'clock—I was to take them to my mother's in Glass House-street, Ratcliffe—I met the pri soner carrying a coat—he said he was tired, and asked me to carry it for him a little way, and he would carry my bundle—he told me to walk on—I came on to the turning by the wooden bridge—he told me to go straight on—I went on a couple of footsteps—I turned and could not see him nor my bundle—I went back, and asked all the people if they had <hi rend="italic">seen</hi> him, they said no.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
